title: The new animal kingdom Japan
subTitle: A young fox tries to find a new territory on the island of Honshu in Japan. Along the way, he encounters a variety of animals trying to adapt to an ever-changing environment.

title: The new animal kingdom Japan
subTitle: Winter has gripped the north of Honshu and Hokkaido. The fox and its partner are expecting a litter of cubs, but it is difficult to find food. They each go their own way in search of food.

title: Race of Life
subTitle: Males and females of some species fight viciously. Though they are usually not trying to kill each other, the fighting can result in death.

title: Race of Life
subTitle: With predators always looking for a meal, their prey must constantly avoid being eaten. Defensive adaptations add to their chances of survival.

title: Race of Life
subTitle: Attack and escape scenarios involving avian predators and their prey, including horizontal speeding and diving to avoid capture.

title: Race of Life
subTitle: Crocodiles are descended from animals that roamed Earth 250 million years ago, while snakes rely on the sun to control their temperature.

title: Extreme Snakes
subTitle: Discover how Australia's resilient population of snakes slithered their way to the top of every ecosystem in one of the harshest and most extreme continents to exist on Earth.

title: Extreme Snakes
subTitle: Meet Africa's diverse but often dangerous species of snake, which have evolved to thrive in the myriad habitats existing within this vast, biodiverse continent.

title: Pride Rules
subTitle: Witness joyous births, shattering deaths and battles galore as the Waterfront Pride fights to maintain control over the banks of Botswana's Chobe River.

title: Cheetah: Against All Odds
subTitle: Follows 2 families of cheetahs struggle against heat, starvation and predators on the Serengeti.

title: Epic Animal Encounters
subTitle: Yasmin Tajik is amazed at how a leopard that has been watching impalas move below the tree it's perched in leaps out in one swift movement and kills one of them.

title: Epic Animal Encounters
subTitle: A regular morning spear fishing turns into a horror film for spear fisherman Eugene van Wyngaardt as he finds himself in a one-on-one situation with a great white shark.

title: River Monsters
subTitle: The disappearance of three men in Russia proves to be a baffling case for Jeremy Wade. He embarks on a trip to the Amur River where he seeks to uncover what happened to them.

title: Alpha
subTitle: An eminent religious leader provides comprehensive insight into the teachings of God, guiding people on the right path.

title: Pride Rules
subTitle: Feel the heat when the pride tries to hunt down adequate food as drought conditions push them (and their prey) dangerously close to death.

title: Epic Animal Encounters
subTitle: There is little room for mistakes when we enter into the wild world of animals. Tourist Ria Cilliers and her husband find themselves sharing their morning coffee with a leopard.

subTitle: Tourist Adam Malski is eager to fulfil his lifelong dream of going shark cage diving with great white shark, but his best sighting comes while he is on the boat.

title: Pride Rules
subTitle: Contend with the challenges of the rainy season, which turns everything green and spoils the lions' camouflage. Watch Einstein fail to make new connections and weigh the pros and cons when Keeza and her cub are kidnapped by rival male Mad-Eye Moody.

title: River Monsters
subTitle: Wade hunts for the Lau-lau, a creature said to swallow men whole.

title: Fear on the Savannah
subTitle: Authorities introduced lions in a rehabilitated national park where only herbivores lived, and fear overtook the park.

title: Lethal Attractions
subTitle: In Africa's wilderness, there's no such thing as a free lunch. Predator and prey are well-matched. A worthwhile meal means going up against gut-gouging horns, venomous fangs and stampeding hooves.

title: Cute to Killer
subTitle: Zimbabwe is the perfect habitat for Africa's finest predator. Follow the development of four cubs, from two weeks to three years old, as they progress from 'Cute to Killer'.

title: Wild Dynasties
subTitle: Growing up in the wild is no easy feat. It takes fiercely protective parents and sometimes an entire squadron, along with a pinch of luck, to ensure these wild babies reach their full potential.

title: Extreme Africa
subTitle: South Africa's Drakensberg is one of the continent's most impressive landscapes. It is home to sharp climatic and ecological gradients as physical conditions change for both land-based creatures and the Raptors that swirl in the skies above.

title: Just Animals
subTitle: Explores the interesting facets, physical features, behaviours and habitats of a wide variety of animal species.

title: The Zoo
subTitle: Located just 10 miles from New York's Times Square, the Bronx Zoo is a recognised world leader in animal care and species conservation. It houses more than 6,000 animals and has a staff of 500-plus people dedicated to their care and well-being. Never before have camera crews been granted full access to the 265-acre campus, until production of the docuseries `The Zoo'. The results are stories focusing on dozens of animals and experiences at the facility, and its critical mission to conserve wildlife around the world. Episodes also highlight various employees and how their expertise and skills help provide top-quality care for the animals.

title: Crikey! It's the Irwins
subTitle: Carrying on late wildlife conservationist Steve Irwin's mission to bring people closer to animals is now the mission of his family. Terri, Bindi and Robert Irwin return to Animal Planet, giving viewers access to their wildlife adventures around the world and the amazing animals that continue to inspire their conservation efforts. The series features the family caring for more than 1,200 animals at the Australia Zoo; overseeing a world-class wildlife hospital, the largest of its kind in the world; and conducting high-level global expeditions.

title: Jewels of the Natural World
subTitle: Explores stunning natural landscapes and how animals act on their protective and fierce nature to survive and reproduce.

title: Into the Wild: India
subTitle: A journey into India's wilderness highlighting some of its most iconic creatures and diverse habitats. Ranging from tundra to extreme desert, rainforest to urban jungle which provide varied ecological and geographical areas for species to survive.
